Creating jobs, lowering costs, fighting inflation, and keeping more money in people’s pockets.
 
We're working to deliver these for American people and families in Build Back Better.

Build Back Better will cut taxes for parents raising kids. It will make Pre-K universal for the first time ever. And it will create local jobs, good-paying jobs, and union jobs. We'll keep working on this important legislation until we get it done.

Build Back Better will provide the largest investment in child care in American history.
 
It will save millions of families thousands of dollars a year.
 
And it will extend the Child Tax Credit.
 
We won't stop working until it's done.

The US and Canada have a long-standing robust relationship, and NY and Canada share much more than a border.

We’re working together to ensure our border policies don't hurt communities at the Canadian border—especially over the holidays.

Build Back Better will help fight the climate crisis with investments in our economy to create good-paying jobs and spur a green, industrial revolution while lowering the cost of energy for Americans

I stood with @LCVoters, @ClimatePower, & more today as we work to get this done https://t.co/mdQgMiFdIl

Stronger economic growth and less inflation. It's simple: If we want to fight inflationary pressures —if we want to lower costs and grow the economy—the best thing we can do is to pass Build Back Better. We're working to get it done. https://t.co/PUKUBbO8B3

The #InfrastructureBill is an investment in New York’s water. It helps address contaminants, replace lead pipes, and eliminate PFAS so that New York State can ensure communities have the clean drinking water they deserve.

Republicans—who spent years under Donald Trump trying to repeal health care and give tax breaks to the ultra-rich—are opposing tax cuts for the middle class while rooting for prices to go up.
 
Democrats are working to pass Build Back Better to lower costs.

President Biden just sent the Kigali Treaty to phase down HFCs to the Senate for ratification.

Phasing out HFCs will go a long way in fighting climate change—HFCs are a potent greenhouse gas, and U.S. industries are already leading the way in manufacturing alternatives.

Today, a leading economist at Moody's said Build Back Better will "help to lift long-term economic growth via stronger productivity and labor force growth, and thus take the edge off of inflation."

We're working to get it done and keep our historic economic recovery going. https://t.co/HfOMjjsBGs

It will deliver on home-and-community-based services.
It will deliver on child care.
It will deliver to help families in America.

Build Back Better will finally empower Medicare to directly negotiate drug prices and lower costs for millions of seniors and American families for vital drugs like insulin, cancer treatments, and so much more. This is so important, and we're working to pass it.

Build Back Better will provide the largest investment in child care ever.
 
It will save many parents thousands of dollars a year.
 
And it will extend the Child Tax Credit.
 
We won't stop working until it's done.

It's very simple: If we want to create more jobs, fight inflation, and help families lower costs—the best thing we can do is pass Build Back Better.
 
We're working to get it done.

Our country took a major step forward to prepare our economy for the challenges of the 21st century.
 
We can now tell the American people that an infrastructure bill is finally here!
 
And we will keep working to pass President Biden's Build Back Better Act.

The #InfrastructureBill means major New York projects—like Gateway, Cross Bronx Expressway, Second Avenue Subway, I-81 in Syracuse, the Inner Loop in Rochester, and more—will be able to get going.

And there are projects as important as these in every state across the country. https://t.co/xKUVmmU6Ap
